  "texts": [
    "They comprise of neuron and synapse circuits implemented using standard CMOS technologies with biologically plausible time constants (from milliseconds to seconds or even minutes) that make them ideal candidates to emulate neural dynamics 76.",
    "Unlike conventional digital technologies, neuromorphic processors implement memory storage co-distributed with the processing, which allows memory and power consumption to be minimized 77.",
    "Moreover, they often support network reconfigurability 17, 78, conveying information as temporal spikes rather than numeric values 79.",
    "Spikes allow sparse and asynchronous communication which relies on the time of firing and enables efficient spatiotemporal pattern discrimination 80.",
    "4 outlines the features of some representative neuromorphic processors."
